LSF

```json
{
  "application": "LSF",
  "details": {
    "queue": "p1",
    "job_name": "train_baseline_model",
    "cores": 32,
    "gpu": "1 (exclusive process)",
    "walltime": "24:00",
    "memory": "11800MB",
    "output_file": "/dtu/p1/johlau/Thesis-Synthex/jobs/lsf10/logs/R-train_baseline_model_%J.out",
    "error_file": "/dtu/p1/johlau/Thesis-Synthex/jobs/lsf10/logs/R-train_baseline_model_%J.err",
    "modules": [
      "cuda/12.2"
    ],
    "commands": [
      "nvidia-smi",
      "python3 /dtu/p1/johlau/Thesis-Synthex/classification/train_model.py --split-idx 0 --model-name baseline --radchest-samples 0 --model-dir /dtu/p1/johlau/Thesis-Synthex/models/ --data-dir /dtu/p1/johlau/Thesis-Synthex/data/ --epochs 30 --learning-rate 0.00001 --batch-size 128",
      "python3 /dtu/p1/johlau/Thesis-Synthex/classification/train_model.py --split-idx 1 --model-name baseline --radchest-samples 0 --model-dir /dtu/p1/johlau/Thesis-Synthex/models/ --data-dir /dtu/p1/johlau/Thesis-Synthex/data/ --epochs 30 --learning-rate 0.00001 --batch-size 128",
      "python3 /dtu/p1/johlau/Thesis-Synthex/classification/train_model.py --split-idx 2 --model-name baseline --radchest-samples 0 --model-dir /dtu/p1/johlau/Thesis-Synthex/models/ --data-dir /dtu/p1/johlau/Thesis-Synthex/data/ --epochs 30 --learning-rate 0.00001 --batch-size 128",
      "python3 /dtu/p1/johlau/Thesis-Synthex/classification/train_model.py --split-idx 3 --model-name baseline --radchest-samples 0 --model-dir /dtu/p1/johlau/Thesis-Synthex/models/ --data-dir /dtu/p1/johlau/Thesis-Synthex/data/ --epochs 30 --learning-rate 0.00001 --batch-size 128",
      "python3 /dtu/p1/johlau/Thesis-Synthex/classification/train_model.py --split-idx 4 --model-name baseline --radchest-samples 0 --model-dir /dtu/p1/johlau/Thesis-Synthex/models/ --data-dir /dtu/p1/johlau/Thesis-Synthex/data/ --epochs 30 --learning-rate 0.00001 --batch-size 128"
    ]
  }
}
```

The script uses LSF (Load Sharing Facility) to manage the execution of the job. The script requests resources like a specific queue, a number of cores, a GPU, and a walltime limit. It also configures output and error files and sends notifications on job completion. It also utilizes the nvidia-smi command to get information about the GPU and loads the CUDA module to enable CUDA functionalities. The script then executes a Python script (`train_model.py`) five times, with different arguments for each execution.
